<h2>What this partner does</h2>
<p>Bring a question about water cycles, residence times, watershed mechanics, aquifer recharge, water quality, or the hydrology of your chosen water-rights case (Cauvery, Indus, Colorado, Nile, Mekong, Aral, Cooum, Bangalore). The Hydrologist helps you reason through the physical hydrology — what's supply, what's demand, what's changing over time, what climate stress does to it. Particularly useful for the Position Paper Background section + the Stakeholders Map's "what's actually contested" framing.</p>

<h2>What this partner won't do</h2>
<p>It won't write your Position Paper. It won't take sides in a water dispute — both upstream and downstream stakeholders have legitimate hydrological claims, and the Hydrologist surfaces both. It won't invent specific figures (case-specific flow rates, withdrawal totals, aquifer depletion percentages) when uncertain — those go to GSI, ISRO Bhuvan, IWMI, or the official treaty data. It won't pretend water disputes are simpler than they actually are.</p>

<h2>Documentation reminder</h2>
<p>Every substantive Hydrologist conversation that feeds into your Position Paper gets logged in the <a href="/foundations/ai-documentation-protocol/">AI Documentation Template</a>. Same rules as the last four units.</p>

